OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FITV News Scotland Correspondent Peter
OL,7,FSmith looks into the shifting politics
OL,8,Faround oil and gas in the North Sea as
OL,9,Fthe US-Iran war drags on and the
OL,10,FScottish election approaches
OL,12,FWith global energy markets in turmoil
OL,13,Fand Scottish voters facing spiralling
OL,14,Fbills, SNP leader John Swinney says
OL,15,Fthe arguments around North Sea
OL,16,Fdrilling have "changed" and he is now
OL,17,Fopen to new oil and gas exploration
OL,18,Foff Scotland's coast.
OL,26,@xD@OOUxD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FIt is a remarkable turnaround for a
OL,7,Fparty that spent the last five years
OL,8,Fmaking the opposite case.
OL,10,F"The arguments I think that have
OL,11,Fchanged in recent weeks have been
OL,12,Fabout the reliability and the security
OL,13,Fof energy supply, which brings in
OL,14,Ffurther considerations that have to be
OL,15,Ftaken into account," Swinney told ITV
OL,16,FNews.
OL,26,@rD@AOUwD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FHe wants energy policy devolved from
OL,7,FWestminster to Holyrood after the
OL,8,Felection, and insists any new project
OL,9,Fwould still face a "climate
OL,10,Fcompatibility test" before winning SNP
OL,11,Fbacking. But he now concedes it may be
OL,12,Fbetter for the environment, as well as
OL,13,Ffor energy security, to produce oil
OL,14,Fand gas in the North Sea rather than
OL,15,Frely on imports shipped from overseas.
OL,17,FThe spiralling cost of energy bills,
OL,18,Fwhile Scotland sits above some of the
OL,19,Flargest untapped reserves in Europe,
OL,20,Fhas also played a part in his
OL,21,Fpolitical recalculation.
OL,26,@qD@TOUrD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FBut his shift is all the more striking
OL,7,Fgiven how strongly the SNP felt about
OL,8,Fthis just a few years ago.
OL,10,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,11,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,12,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,13,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/17
