PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FRosebank is the largest untapped
OL,7,Foilfield in Britain, estimated to hold
OL,8,Faround 300 million barrels of
OL,9,Frecoverable reserves over a lifespan
OL,10,Fof roughly 25 years.
OL,12,FOil is sold on international markets,
OL,13,Fand so new oil fields in Britain are
OL,14,Funlikely to have any impact on
OL,15,Fhousehold bills, but the UK can
OL,16,Fgenerate significant revenue from
OL,17,Fproduction.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31912
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FGas is different: it is not traded
OL,7,Finternationally and can be kept within
OL,8,Fthe UK. If Jackdaw is approved, the
OL,9,Fgas from this field could be pumped to
OL,10,Fthe mainland and heating British homes
OL,11,Fby this winter.
OL,13,FBoth Rosebank and Jackdaw were
OL,14,Fpreviously approved, but environmental
OL,15,Fgroups Greenpeace and Uplift
OL,16,Fsuccessfully challenged those
OL,17,Fdecisions in court, arguing that the
OL,18,Fenvironmental impact assessments had
OL,19,Ffailed to account for the emissions
OL,20,Fproduced when the fuel is actually
OL,21,Fburned.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31913
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FFollowing a Supreme Court ruling, the
OL,7,FUK government conceded the approvals
OL,8,Fwere unlawful. Both developers must
OL,9,Fnow reapply, this time accounting for
OL,10,Fthose emissions. The projects remain
OL,11,Fin legal and regulatory limbo, which
OL,12,Fis precisely what makes them such a
OL,13,Flive issue in this election.
OL,15,FSupporters of new drilling argue that
OL,16,Fproducing gas at home is cleaner than
OL,17,Fimporting it.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31914
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FAnalysis by the North Sea Transition
OL,7,FAuthority showed how domestically
OL,8,Fproduced gas, which is measured in
OL,9,F'carbon intensity', comes in at around
OL,10,F21kg of CO2 per barrel of oil
OL,11,Fequivalent, compared to an average of
OL,12,F79kg for liquefied natural gas shipped
OL,13,Fin from overseas.
OL,15,FIt seems simple, but it's not quite
OL,16,Fthat straightforward when it comes to
OL,17,Fthe decision making over the North Sea
OL,18,Findustry.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31915
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FFor example, the majority of UK gas
OL,7,Fimports currently arrive via pipeline
OL,8,Ffrom Norway, which has lower emissions
OL,9,Fthan North Sea production.
OL,11,FThe Climate Change Committee also
OL,12,Fwarned that any emissions advantage
OL,13,Ffrom domestic production could be
OL,14,Fwiped out if increased UK output
OL,15,Fsimply leads to more fossil fuel
OL,16,Fconsumption overall, at a time when
OL,17,Fthe UK is meant to be transitioning to
OL,18,Frenewables and an electric economy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31916
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776477807
OL,3,CScotland's North Sea dilemma: Where
OL,4,Crising bills meet rising tides
OL,6,FThere is also a political reality
OL,7,Fbehind any decisions, and many parties
OL,8,Fare more cognisant of monitoring the
OL,9,Fpublic mood than measuring carbon
OL,10,Femissions during an election period.
OL,12,FPolling in Scotland just now
OL,13,Fconsistently shows voters are more
OL,14,Fimmediately worried about the cost of
OL,15,Fliving than the long-term consequences
OL,16,Fof climate change. For many, rising
OL,17,Fenergy bills feel more urgent than
OL,18,Frising sea levels.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
